reviews.name: John Ladasky
reviews.text:
This Charge Point always has several open chargers! That's the good news. The bad news: getting a connection is problematic. I haven't figured out whether certain chargers are simply turned off, whether they only operate at certain times of the day or week, or whether they're just broken.

EDIT: I've continued to use this Charge Point for several years.  the problem I noted in 2021 seemed to disappear.  One weekday evening in 2024 though, the situation that prompted my initial review repeated.  I received notifications that my car had stopped charging multiple times.  These were not false warnings, my car really did stop charging for up to 30 minutes at a time.  And then, equally mysteriously, charging would resume, only to shut off again 15 to 30 minutes later.

reviews.text:
Finally found a V4 supercharger in San Jose and it’s in the Willow Glen Plaza parking lot.
Came here at 9AM on a weekend and was able to find a charging spot pretty easily. There are 12 v4 supercharger units at this location. The charging lasted for 25 minutes (from 17% to 80%) I got 200-225kW until 40% and above 100kW until 60% of battery charging. I got at least 70kW all the way till 80% of battery charging!

So if you’re here for a quick refill from under 20% to get to 60%, you should be able to get it with around 15 minutes of charging. Willow Glen Plaza has a Starbucks too, so you can make a quick coffee break

questionsAndAnswers.question: How long does it take to charge my electric car at Valero

answers.answer: Depends on your vehicle, how empty your battery is, and how much charge is coming through at any given moment to your vehicle. All these factors determine the length of time needed to charge your car.
